{
  "stem": "2723.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I really wasn't conscious, because it was kept away from me to a great degree, until the age of about 11.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I wasn't very physically, bodily, aware of anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I think I became aware.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It hit with a clang, in 1939, that something was very wrong.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Because we were having a family Seder.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And my father, who had been in the army, in World War I, had made a very personal friendship with a most unlikely man, who was certainly nowhere near my father's educational equal, who knocked on our door, and came to warn my father in the middle of our Seder that he was blacklisted.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The man that came to us was a member of the Nazi party.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And he came to warn my father that because of his known [NON-ENGLISH] involvement, he was branded anti-social, Zionistic, whatever.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And he gave my father the chance to disappear.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "My father had a passport.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And he left a week after Pesach, in '39, which brought things down, I suppose, into a different dimension altogether.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Because from that day on, it was mother, sister, and I.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And our lives became very different.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the beginning, I suppose, the shock value and the loss my father's absence created was so strong that I didn't realize the struggles my mother had to go through.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] My grandmother was no longer alive.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One of my aunts, my mother's youngest sister, was sent to England.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She was a very bright woman and got somehow into Cambridge.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And her dispatch and sending away took a lot of energy from in the family.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then my mother, grandmother, and aunt were the ones who were sort of busying themselves around me and trying to fill the gap my father's absence had left.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
